  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok or large frying pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add chili flakes, garlic, ginger, and peanuts to the pan; stir-fry for about 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Pour in soy sauce, rice vinegar, brown sugar, and chili sauce. Bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low-medium and simmer for another 5 minutes while stirring occasionally.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed (add more salt if preferred).",
    "Add tapioca pearls to the pan; stir-fry for about 2-3 minutes until they start to swell.",
    "Fold in almonds, mix well and let cook for an additional minute.",
    "Serve hot immediately."
